{"id":504189,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_S._Wistrich","text":"Robert Solomon Wistrich (April 7, 1945 \u2013 May 19, 2015) was a British-Israeli academic and author. He was a leading scholar of antisemitism in Europe. He was also the Neuburger Professor of European and Jewish history at the Hebrew University of Jerusalem. He wrote and edited at least 30 books.\nWistrich was born in Lenger, Kazakh SSR (now Kazakhstan). His parents were leftist Polish Jews who moved to escape antisemitism. He later moved to France with his family, and grew up in England.\nWistrich died from a heart attack on May 19, 2015 in Rome, Italy. He was 70.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"British_people","surface_form":"British","offset":61},{"uri":"Israelis","surface_form":"Israeli","offset":69},{"uri":"Academic","surface_form":"academic","offset":77},{"uri":"Author","surface_form":"author","offset":90},{"uri":"Scholar","surface_form":"scholar","offset":115},{"uri":"Antisemitism","surface_form":"antisemitism","offset":126},{"uri":"European_history","surface_form":"European","offset":189},{"uri":"Jewish_history","surface_form":"Jewish history","offset":202},{"uri":"Hebrew_University_of_Jerusalem","surface_form":"Hebrew University","offset":224},{"uri":"Jerusalem","surface_form":"Jerusalem","offset":245},{"uri":"Lenger","surface_form":"Lenger","offset":316},{"uri":"Kazakh_Soviet_Socialist_Republic","surface_form":"Kazakh SSR","offset":324},{"uri":"Kazakhstan","surface_form":"Kazakhstan","offset":340},{"uri":"Poles","surface_form":"Polish","offset":378},{"uri":"Jews","surface_form":"Jews","offset":385},{"uri":"France","surface_form":"France","offset":442},{"uri":"England","surface_form":"England","offset":481},{"uri":"Heart_attack","surface_form":"heart attack","offset":511},{"uri":"Rome","surface_form":"Rome","offset":543},{"uri":"Italy","surface_form":"Italy","offset":549}]}